58–1485":"1458–1485","1536":"1536","1502":"1502","1458":"1458","1456":"1456","1475":"1475","1496":"1496","1474":"1474","1485":"1485","1494":"1494","1480":"1480","July 1485":"July 1485","1559":"1559","Dedham, Colchester district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Dedham, , Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ravens","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (London): variant of   Raven  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Raven","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Raven</i> (Old Norse <i>Hrafn</i>, Old English <i>Hræfn</i>, both meaning ‘raven’) or else a nickname from this word, probably denoting a dark-haired man.","English: occasionally perhaps also a topographic or habitational name referring to a house or inn distinguished by the sign of a raven (see 1 above). Surnames derived from house and inn signs are rare in English.","North German and Dutch: from Middle Low German <i>rave(n)</i> ‘raven’, a nickname or an old personal name. Compare 1 above."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Ravens was born in 1475, in Dedham, Essex, England, his father, Richard Ravens, was 19 and his mother, Alice, was 17. He married JoHanna E. Starlying in 1494, in Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1502, in Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 27."},"et":{"1475–1502":"1475–1502","1480–1536":"1480–1536","1494–1559":"1494–1559","1456–1496":"1456–1496","1458–1485":"1458–1485","1536":"1536","1502":"1502","1458":"1458","1456":"1456","1475":"1475","1496":"1496","1474":"1474","1485":"1485","1494":"1494","1480":"1480","July 1485":"juuli 1485","1559":"1559","Dedham, Colchester district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dedham, , Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1475–1502":"1475–1502","1480–1536":"1480–1536","1494–1559":"1494–1559","1456–1496":"1456–1496","1458–1485":"1458–1485","1536":"1536","1502":"1502","1458":"1458","1456":"1456","1475":"1475","1496":"1496","1474":"1474","1485":"1485","1494":"1494","1480":"1480","July 1485":"heinäkuu 1485","1559":"1559","Dedham, Colchester district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dedham, , Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1475–1502":"1475–1502","1480–1536":"1480–1536","1494–1559":"1494–1559","1456–1496":"1456–1496","1458–1485":"1458–1485","1536":"1536","1502":"1502","1458":"1458","1456":"1456","1475":"1475","1496":"1496","1474":"1474","1485":"1485","1494":"1494","1480":"1480","July 1485":"juillet 1485","1559":"1559","Dedham, Colchester district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Dedham, 